text: Floating Empty in the Void

I dont put these expectations on anyone else but myself, all because of the way people talked to me as a child. Really wish the brain wasnt so complicated so myself and others werent still battling these things decades later.
I fail at this almost everyday, but having to talk back to these old voices that no longer matter is so tiring! Its slowly working, just a hard uphill battle.

Having to unlearn things taught to me growing up is exhausting, that my worth as a person isnt determined by my job, my beauty (or lack of) my weight, or my age. I can exist in any form at all and still be a worthwhile person.

Anyway I dunno why I'm putting this on my public feed, I am just so exhausted from wanting to isolate myself further. But doing the opposite feels wrong too

I grew up with an emotionally distant parent, i solved all my problems by myself. I told no one about my struggles because no one listened. So now when i feel bad, I just want to remove myself from everyones circles. The urge is too strong sometimes, especially lately.
When you're used to self isolating, how do you stop? I just want to withdraw when i feel terrible, but ill be alone forever if i keep that up.
